INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Krueger, S.1673, and Assembly Member Lopez, A.4069, “AN ACT to amend the local emergency housing rent control act, in relation to rent regulation laws”.
EventItemMatterName: Local emergency housing rent control act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature adopt, and the Governor to sign, A.9550/S.6539 which would provide homeowners in New York City an abatement of real property taxes for the installation cost of sewer improvement check valve devices.
EventItemMatterName: Provide homeowners in New York City an abatement of real property taxes for the installation cost of sewer improvement check valve devices.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.3244-A, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.5754-A, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to allowing members of the New York city employees’ retirement system and the New York city board of education employees’ retirement system to elect the benefits provided by chapter 96 of the laws of 1995”.
EventItemMatterName: NYCERS and BOEERS elect benefits provided by Chapter 96 of 1995 (S.3244-A, A.5754-A).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.4894-A, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.7063-A, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to the application of the age fifty-seven retirement program, the mandated physically taxing program, and the incumbent fifty-five/twenty-five program for certain employees”.
EventItemMatterName: Fifty-seven retirement program (S.4894-A, A.7063-A).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.6211-A, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.8449-A, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to providing benefit enhancements to certain members of retirement systems in the city of New York”.
EventItemMatterName: Benefit enhancements to certain members of city retirement systems (S.6211-A, A.8449-A).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Padavan, S.3314-A, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.5961-A, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to coverage for additional members of the New York city employees’ retirement system”.
EventItemMatterName: Coverage for additional members of the NYCERS (S.3314-A, A.5961-A).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Maltese, S.6861, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.8377-A, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, the administrative code of the city of New York and the education law, in relation to the establishment of a twenty-five year retirement program for members of the New York city employees’ retirement system or the board of education retirement system of the city of New York employed in construction laborer positions.”.
EventItemMatterName: Twenty-five year program for members of NYCERS or BOERS of New York employed in construction laborer positions (S.6861, A.8377-A).

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of meat from animals produced by cloning.
EventItemMatterName: The sale of meat from animals produced by cloning.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey to provide inductive loop Assistive Listening Systems in New York City’s airports, John F. Kennedy International Airport and La Guardia Airport, to allow for the improved broadcast of airport information, instructions, and safety notices to hearing impaired individuals.
EventItemMatterName: Provide inductive loop Assistive Listening Systems in New York City’s airports, John F. Kennedy International Airport and La Guardia Airport.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the tow advisory board.
EventItemMatterName: Tow advisory board.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to rates for the towing of motor vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Rates for the towing of motor vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reflective vests for commercial bicyclists.
EventItemMatterName: Reflective vests for commercial bicyclists.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution concerning the establishment of the Park Slope Fifth Avenue Business Improvement District in the Borough of Brooklyn and setting the date, time and place for the public hearing to hear all persons interested in the establishment of such district.
EventItemMatterName: Park Slope Fifth Avenue BID in the Borough of Brooklyn.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring information on working conditions from foreign manufacturers of goods.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring information on working conditions from foreign manufacturers of goods.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Fire Department of the City of New York to send bi-annual written notice to all residents of New York City reminding them to check the operation of their smoke alarms and carbon monoxide detectors and other fire prevention information.
EventItemMatterName: FDNY  to send bi-annual written notice to all residents of NYC reminding them to check the operation of their smoke alarms and carbon monoxide detectors and other fire prevention information.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that the affidavits required for the filing of a real property transfer tax return on the sale of one- or two- family dwellings as well as cooperative and condominium apartments indicate that the premises sold is equipped with an operational carbon monoxide detecting device as well as a smoke detecting device.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of one- or two- family dwellings as well as cooperative and condominium apartments indicate that the premises sold is equipped with an operational carbon monoxide detecting device as well as a smoke detecting device.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and adopt, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would authorize the city of New York to establish a Small Performance Venue Business Tax Credit.
EventItemMatterName: Authorize the city of New York to establish a Small Performance Venue Business Tax Credit.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to incorporate the Muslim holidays of Eid Ul-Fitr and Eid Ul-Adha as observed school holidays in the school calendar for the city school district of the city of New York, and calling upon the State legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign into law, A.8108/S.5837, an Act to amend the education law, in relation to requiring that Eid Ul-Fitr and Eid Ul-Adha be school holidays in the city school district of the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Department of Education to incorporate the Muslim holidays of Eid Ul-Fitr and Eid Ul-Adha as observed school holidays.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Cultural Affairs to ensure the equitable distribution of funds to cultural organizations, greater transparency in the funding of these organizations and diverse representation within all entities that determine funding to cultural organizations.
EventItemMatterName: Ensure the equitable distribution of funds to cultural organizations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State of New York to pass A.3873/S.1865, legislation that would amend the Administrative Code of the City of New York and the retirement and social security law by expanding the term “physically taxing occupation” to include registered nurses and midwives employed by the City of New York or the New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation.
EventItemMatterName: Expanding the term “physically taxing occupation” to include registered nurses and midwives employed by the City of New York or the NYC HHC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing a credit against the commercial rent or occupancy tax imposed by chapter 7 of title 11 of such code, to tenants who provide employer-provided child care.
EventItemMatterName: Providing a credit against the commercial rent or occupancy tax imposed by chapter 7 of title 11 of such code, to tenants who provide employer-provided child care.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to enact legislation authorizing the city of New York to provide tax incentives to businesses that offer child care assistance to employees.
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing the city of New York to provide tax incentives to businesses that offer child care assistance to employees.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to healthcare expenses for certain 9/11 workers.
EventItemMatterName: Healthcare expenses for certain 9/11 workers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to real estate advertising in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Real estate advertising in New York City.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the display of the POW/MIA flag on all city buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Display of the POW/MIA flag on all city buildings that display the American flag.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to new hybrid electric vehicle parking.
EventItemMatterName: New hybrid electric vehicle parking.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution officially designating “Gotham City” as the nickname of New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Officially designating “Gotham City” as the nickname of New York City.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature and the Governor to amend the New York State Tax Law to authorize the City of New York to provide an income tax credit equal to $100 for the purchase of gasoline for hybrid vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the NYS Tax Law to authorize NYC to provide an income tax credit equal to $100 for the purchase of gasoline for hybrid vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would provide a sales and compensating use tax exemption for the purchase of hybrid vehicles.
